                            <comment id="12909731" author="curtisr7" created="Wed, 15 Sep 2010 14:48:59 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Per the spec : &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; If SUM, AVG, MAX, or MIN is used, and there are no values to which the aggregate function can be applied, the result of the aggregate function is NULL.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Something else to muddy the waters....&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; The Java type that is contained in the result of a query using an aggregate function is as follows:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; ...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; *MAX, MIN return the type of the state field to which they are applied.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the example detailed above, lets say the p.pk field is a primitive long... A NULL primitive is zero so in that case, it would appear that we are working properly. If p.pk is a java.lang.Long, we are not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12910602" author="oakjumper" created="Fri, 17 Sep 2010 15:17:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;it&apos;s 0 for Integer field.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
